{{Infobox prepared food|name=Aprapransa|image=Aprapransa.jpg|caption=Aprapransa garnished with crabs|alternate_name=|country=[[Ghana]]|creator=GaDangme people|course=|served=Hot|main_ingredient=Corn dough, beans, onion, tomatoes, fermented salted fish, smoked fish, palm oil, pepper, salt and crab|variations=|calories=|other=}}'''Aprapransa''' is a local dish of the people from the Greater Accra Region of Ghana. It is basically made from roasted corn flour, cooked beans together with other ingredients (onion, tomatoes, fermented salted fish, smoked fish, palm oil, pepper, salt and crab). Its a food that is served on special occasions and is feared to go extinct.

Aprapransa nnyɛ aduane a abu so wɔ mmɔnten so a wɔ tontɔn wɔ Ghana anaa aduane a wɔtaa noa no mpɛn pii wɔ afie mu. Mpen pii no, Akanfo ne wɔn a wɔ kyekyɛ aduane yi wɔ nna titiriw te sɛ ayeforohyia ase, abadintoɔ ase, awodadi bre, mmusua hyia da ne nea ɛkeka ho

== Akadeɛ ==
1.    Aburo a y’akye esam kuruwa mienu

2.    Ngo kɔkɔɔ kwantere baako

3.    Tomantose akɛseɛ mienu

4.    Gyenne keseɛ baako

5.    Adwen a y’ahow

6.    Koobi anaa mɔmɔne baako

7.    Adua kuruwa fa

8.    Nkyene ne mako

9.    Kɔtɔ

